SIMPLE: manhood
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Manhood
<hw>Man"hood</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Man-</ets> +
<ets>-hood</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being man as a
human being, or man as distinguished from a child or a woman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Manly quality; virility; courage; bravery;
resolution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am ashamed⟦br⟧
That thou hast power to shake my <qex>manhood</qex> thus.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The genitalia of a male human.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The condition of being a human being.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>man-hour</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>man hour</ent>⟦br⟧
<mhw>
